** I like the idea of replacing mud spells with these attack abilities.  That's
** the same thing I had in mind with things like intimidate, assault, backstab,
** strangle, sharpshoot, execute (this one would be a finishing move of sorts).
** We can decide which ones we like the best, or just use all of them.  Gangbang
** and drive_by were also meant to be attack abilities, but only when in groups.

INNER GUILD ABILITIES:
     These abilities are mainly for use to facilitate role-play and the
mechanics of the guild.  The are gained not through guild level but by
the accumulated graft of the mobster.
     ice: puts a mobster 'on ice' preventing him/her from using most
          guild powers.
     contract: Offers a specific amount of graft for the death of a target
     contracts: Shows a list of current open contracts.
     plate: puts a plate on the table for any family member.
     feast: Fills a table at the family resturant full of food/drink :)
     account: Shows the Boss an accounting of the families graft.
** These are great!  I'm not sure I totally understand how plate and feast would
** work - sounds like some sort of healing ability.  Ice and contracts are really
** great ideas.

GUILD WEAPON:
     The Thomson sub-machine gun.  AKA tommy gun.  Takes a drum
magazine of 45 caliber shells guaranteed to rip the guts out of
anyone dumb enough to get in the way!
** After reading /doc/build/RULES/GUILD_WEAPON, I'm assuming that you are thinking
** of this as a non-exclusive weapon.  I would think that guild members should be
** able to use other weapons as well, and maybe get bonuses for using knives or
** any other gun.  Also, in order to give the weapon a greater damage potential,
** a random error could be built in for possible misfire/backfire/ammo jam.

GUILD PET:
     The guilds pet will take the form of a street punk.  a 'runner'
for the mobster.  He will not take part in combat.  Used to send
things to ppl and to carry stuff. (bagman).
** I hadn't considered this, but it sounds good.  Sounds very similar to the
** Vampire servants and could probably be coded in the same way.

GUILD HIERARCHY:
     Success in the Mob is measured in two parts, the common guild
leveland the inner organizational 'title'.
     Guild levels are raised through the trade of graft and exp while
the mobsters title is is determined by a graft payment, availability
and the word of the Godfather/Don/Leiutenant respectively.
     Example guild levels are: Bullie, Thug, Muscle, Racketeer, Mobster,
Wiseguy.
     The titles are: Godfather (wiz), Don (Territorial Crime Boss),
Leiutenant, Hit-Man, Soldier.
     There are also two special designations: Made, and Retired.
To attack a made man in any family is to invite a contract from the
Godfather.  Made men who cause trouble are usually Retired to a boat
near some tropical island...
** I definitely agree with all of this.  I think this is what will really give the
** guild style and make players want to be a part of it.

DISADVANTAGES:
     To be more than a soldier one must keep pk set.
     When a mobster dies they are returned to 'soldier'.
     Players may pk others in the guild.
     The amount of families and the measure of thier numbers are constant.
** These sound pretty good.  I also think making the guild 'no teleport' would
** fit well with the theme.  I don't understand the last disadvantage that you
** have listed.

ADVANTAGES:
     The ability to garnish coins from other players.
** I like this, but I don't see how it would work.  This is along the same lines
** of what I was thinking with the pickpocket, steal, and kidnap abilities.
